import React from 'react' import Timeline from '@mui/lab/Timeline'; import TimelineItem from '@mui/lab/TimelineItem'; import TimelineSeparator from '@mui/lab/TimelineSeparator'; import TimelineConnector from '@mui/lab/TimelineConnector'; import TimelineContent from '@mui/lab/TimelineContent'; import TimelineDot from '@mui/lab/TimelineDot'; import TimelineOppositeContent from '@mui/lab/TimelineOppositeContent'; import { createTheme, ThemeProvider, Typography } from '@mui/material'; import LottieAnimation from '../../../lottieScripts/LottieAnimation'; import historyanimationData1 from "../../../assets/LottieJson/history/history1.json"; import styled from 'styled-components'; import { Box } from '@mui/system'; const theme = createTheme({ typography: { fontFamily: [ 'Poppins', 'sans-serif' ].join(','), } }); theme.typography.h5 = { fontSize: '1em', [theme.breakpoints.up('lg')]: { fontSize: '1em', width: '21vw' }, [theme.breakpoints.down('lg')]: { fontSize: '1em', width: '24vw' }, [theme.breakpoints.down('md')]: { fontSize: '0.875em', width: '27vw' }, [theme.breakpoints.down('sm')]: { fontSize: '0.75em', width: '30vw' }, [theme.breakpoints.down('xs')]: { fontSize: '0.6em', width: '33vw' }, }; const VideoContainerLeft = styled.div` width: 24vw; float: right; ` theme.TimelineOppositeContent = { zIndex: '-1' } const MyTimeline = () => { return ( 4th Century BC, Greece

The first description of bodies falling downwards towards the centre was related to their nature was documented by the Greek philosopher Aristotle. This nature of objects getting attracted was due to their gravitas or heaviness. 10:00 am 3rd Century BC, Greece

Archimedes discovered the centre of mass of a triangle and postulated the centre of mass of 2 equal weighing objects. 12:00 am 7th century AD, India

Brahmagupta called this invisible force of attraction“gurutvaakarshan”. 9:00 am 1589 - 1592 AD, Italy

Galileo Galilei showed that gravitational acceleration is the same for all falling objects. In short, all objects would fall at the same rate, if not for air resistance. He did that by dropping balls from the leaning Tower of Pisa. 09:30 am 1687 AD, England

Sir Isaac Newton derived the Universal Law of Gravitation in “Principia”. 10:00 am Code 12:00 am Sleep 9:00 am Repeat ) } export default MyTimeline
